## NCBI (National Center for Biotechnology Information)
📌 Purpose

NCBI is one of the largest biological databases used for retrieving nucleotide sequences, protein information, genome data, literature, and bioinformatics tools.

## 📌 Major Databases
GenBank
RefSeq
PubMed
Gene
Protein
SRA
## 📌 Common Uses
Retrieve DNA/RNA sequences
Download protein sequences
Literature search
Sequence annotation
BLAST analysis
## 📌 Important File Formats
FASTA (.fasta)
GenBank (.gb)
TXT
## 📌 Steps for Sequence Retrieval
Open NCBI website
Select database (Nucleotide/Protein)
Search using accession number
Open sequence record
Download FASTA format
## 📌 Output Files to Upload
FASTA sequences
GenBank records
Screenshots
Accession lists
